&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dock Sortation Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Operations · On-Site (Saltbox Location)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Saltbox is on a mission to simplify the hardest parts of running an eCommerce business. Our purpose-built spaces serve as modern headquarters for small to medium-sized businesses in industries like Fashion &amp;amp; Apparel, Health &amp;amp; Beauty, Electronics, and Household Goods. We offer a powerful combination of flexible warehouse suites, offices, and on-site logistics support that empower entrepreneurs to scale with confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re launching something new at Saltbox—and we need the right people to run it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Dock Sortation Specialist, you’re the execution engine of our new Dock Sorting function. You’re on the floor every shift—scanning packages, sorting them accurately, staging them for drivers, and making sure every package gets where it needs to go, on time. This is a fast-paced, physical, detail-oriented role where accuracy and reliability aren’t just nice to have—they’re everything.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work alongside a small, tight-knit crew processing hundreds of packages per shift using handheld scanning technology. When the day is done, you may also pitch in to support other parts of the Saltbox operation—from member logistics to building upkeep—as part of our Elastic Workforce (e-Force). You’ll report to the Dock Sortation Lead at your location, with support from the Saltbox Operational Excellence team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Package Scanning &amp;amp; Sortation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scan every inbound package using the Sort App on a handheld device—each package gets two scans: presort and bin assignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a target scan rate of 225 scans per hour (approximately 112 packages processed per hour).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sort packages into the correct shelving unit or bin based on batch and market assignment. Accuracy is critical—missorts delay drivers and risk SLA breaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staging &amp;amp; Dispatch&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Move sorted batches to the driver handoff zone before the dispatch window opens.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with dispatch scanning as drivers pick up their loads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help ensure 99.5% of packages are dispatched by 11:00am.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Driver Handoff &amp;amp; End-of-Shift Reconciliation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the Lead with driver coordination—staging packages for pickup, completing departure scans, and keeping the handoff zone organized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help count on-hand packages at shift end and immediately flag any discrepancies to the Lead.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Workspace Stewardship&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep the sortation area clean, organized, and safe throughout your shift.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Return equipment to proper positions and maintain the Saltbox standard for Members and partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
